						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the Kailāsanātha temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-Chōḷadēva: Year 17 = 1199-1200 A.D. (?)</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a grant of land made by a certain Śiṅgaṉśōḻaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Anuttarap-Pallavaraiyan, a Tenkuḍuba, for daily food-offerings to the goddess Tribhuvanasundara-nāchchiyār in Kaṇṇāḍipputtūr in Karaivaḻi-nāḍu.</p>						

